{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/variant\/takeref()"]}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant\/VariantProtocol-Implementations"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant\/takeRef()"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:4GLib15VariantProtocolPAAE7takeRefAA0bE0VSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib7VariantC","roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"takeRef()","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"VariantRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariantRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Typically you want to use "},{"code":"g_variant_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in order to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"automatically do the correct thing with respect to floating or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"non-floating references, but there is one specific scenario where"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this function is helpful."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The situation where this function is helpful is when creating an API"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"text":".  We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"where the value that is being returned already exists)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"At the same time, the style of the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" API makes it likely that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for newly-created "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"text":" instances, the user can be saved some","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"typing if they are allowed to return a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" with a floating"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reference.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Using this function on the return value of the user’s callback allows","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them.  The caller"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will always receives exactly one full reference to the value: either","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that has been converted to a full reference.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_variant_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" running at the same time in another thread on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the same ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":" instance.  If "},{"code":"g_variant_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" runs first then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference.  If "},{"code":"g_variant_take_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then the result will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"be that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"an additional reference on top of that one is added.  It is best to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"avoid this situation.","type":"text"}]}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Variant":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variant","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","kind":"symbol","title":"Variant","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Variant","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Variant","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GVariant","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a variant datatype; it can contain one or more values","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"along with information about the type of the values.","type":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Variant/VariantProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant\/VariantProtocol-Implementations","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variant\/variantprotocol-implementations","title":"VariantProtocol Implementations"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/VariantRef":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"VariantRef"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VariantRef"}],"title":"VariantRef","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variantref","abstract":[{"code":"GVariant","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a variant datatype; it can contain one or more values"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"along with information about the type of the values."}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Variant/takeRef()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant\/takeRef()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variant\/takeref()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"VariantRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"title":"takeRef()","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol"}}}